BT /F1 12 Tf 50 750 Td (JWT Vulnerabilities - Short Research Report) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 736 Td () Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 722 Td (Overview:) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 708 Td (JSON Web Tokens \(JWTs\) are commonly used for stateless authentication.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 694 Td (If implemented incorrectly, JWTs expose multiple vulnerabilities.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 680 Td () Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 666 Td (Common vulnerabilities:) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 652 Td (1\) alg=none / Signature stripping - Some verifiers accept 'alg=none' and mark tokens valid without verification.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 638 Td (2\) Weak secrets - Short or guessable HMAC secrets let attackers forge valid tokens by signing payloads.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 624 Td (3\) Key confusion - Allowing algorithm switching \(e.g., RS256 <-> HS256\) may let attackers use public keys as HMAC secrets.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 610 Td (4\) Replay attacks - Long-lived tokens can be reused; lack of nonce/exp checks enables replay.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 596 Td (5\) Claim tampering and missing validation - Not validating `exp`, `nbf`, `iss`, `aud` allows unauthorized access.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 582 Td () Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 568 Td (Mitigations:) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 554 Td (- Always validate the algorithm and restrict to specific algorithms \(e.g., HS256 or RS256\), never accept 'none'.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 540 Td (- Use strong, high-entropy secrets for HMAC \(>= 256 bits recommended\) and protect private keys.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 526 Td (- Prefer asymmetric signatures \(RS256/ES256\) for third-party token issuance; carefully handle key usage.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 512 Td (- Validate token claims \(`exp`, `nbf`, `iat`, `aud`, `iss`\) and implement short token lifetimes with refresh tokens.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 498 Td (- Use token revocation lists or sliding windows and implement nonce/UUID to prevent replay when needed.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 484 Td (- Use libraries that perform safe checks \(constant-time compare, disallow dynamic alg selection\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 470 Td () Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 456 Td (References:) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 442 Td (- RFC 7519 \(JSON Web Token\) - IETF.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 428 Td (- OWASP JSON Web Token Cheat Sheet - OWASP Foundation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 414 Td () Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 400 Td (Conclusion:) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 386 Td (JWTs are convenient but dangerous if validators are naive. Follow the mitigations above) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 372 Td (and use vetted libraries and secure key management.) Tj ET
